<head>MOAT</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">護城河</item>
        <item xml:lang="och">池</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>CANAL PRODUCED FOR DEFENDING A CITY.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for a moat designed for military defense is chí 池.</p>
<p>2. Gōu 溝 often refers to any kind of canal, but can be used in particular for defensive canals, especially those not built in conjunction with city walls.</p>
        </div>
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006</p>
<p>ARCHITECTURE 2. 我國從上古至宋代的城牆都是夯土牆，泥土就地挖取，故有城牆必有護城河。護城河中古前常稱 “ 池 ” ，與 “ 城 ” 並用。</p>
<p>魏晉後，常稱 “ 壕 ” ，範圍大於 “ 池 ” ，有更明確的軍事防禦性質。</p>
<p>塹，指深險難越的護城河。</p>
<p>隍，水乾涸的護城河。</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>護城河</p>
<p>城池</p>
<p>城壕</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
